Title: The exact asymptotic of the collision time tail distribution for
  independent Brownian particles with different drifts
Authors: Zbigniew Pucha{\l}a and Tomasz Rolski
Categories: math.PR
Comments: 20 pages
MSC-class: 60J65
Journal-ref: Probab. Theor. Relat. Field., Vol. 142, No. 3-4, pp. 595-617,
  (2008)
DOI: 10.1007/s00440-007-0116-8
\\
  In this note we consider the time of the collision $\tau$ for $n$ independent
Brownian motions $X^1_t,...,X_t^n$ with drifts $a_1,...,a_n$, each starting
from $x=(x_1,...,x_n)$, where $x_1<...<x_n$. We show the exact asymptotics of
$P_x(\tau>t) = C h(x)t^{-\alpha}e^{-\gamma t}(1 + o(1))$ as $t\to\infty$ and
identify $C,h(x),\alpha,\gamma$ in terms of the drifts.
